{
  "text": "In this manuscript, we first present a new heuristic algorithm to find the optimal partition of branches and estimate parameters of substitution matrices. This algorithm benefits from an initial step of substitution mapping [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and is implemented in C++ using the Bio++ libraries [CITATION_4] . Then, using simulations, we show that our approach is both fast and accurate. We apply our methods to previously published data sets, compare it with other approaches, and demonstrate that our new algorithms allow one to reveal the phenotypic determinants of sequence evolution for a wide range of experimental conditions, including large data sets.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1457695",
